The judge gave her
the longest possible sentence he could, but he said Anthony could 
go free on July 17 because she has already served nearly three years and
will get credit for good behaviour.

But Fernandez-Gonzalez's lawyers 
want the court to compel her to appear at a deposition on July 19, because they are concerned when 
she is released from prison on Sunday she will 'leave the jurisdiction 
of this court, disguise herself, change her name, etc., making it 
impossible to ever depose her.'

Mr Morgan said: 'When
Zenaida first came to me, we never thought Casey would see the light of
day again. It was never about money in the beginning. Now, it's about 
accountability and responsibility.'

The civil trial is due to begin in February.

